baseline_groups.claim_summary: Subjects bid significantly higher in Common Value (CV) auctions than in economically equivalent Common Probability (CP) auctions, as measured by bid factor deviations from theoretical benchmarks.
baseline_groups.notes: Three baseline rows correspond to three equivalent outcome measures (BF, BEBF, NEBF) all measuring the same overbidding concept against different benchmarks. All from Experiment 1 main sample with near-identical coefficients (~15.1). Treated as a single baseline group.

global_notes: Clean experimental economics paper with a single core claim across 133 specs. Three baseline outcomes are nearly identical. Heterogeneity analyses classified as non-core. Cross-experiment replications classified as core sample restrictions. Placebo/balance tests clearly non-core.
